KEY:
'-' = Not Completed
'X' = Completed
'*X' = In Progress

Create Objects:
X Floor (Textured)
X 4 Walls, 1 Ceiling (All Colored/Textured)
X Textured Table (Top + 4 Legs)
X Desk Lamp
X Copper Ball
X Polished Silver Ball
X Pair of Dice (with texture-mapped dots)
X Textured picture on the wall (when lights are off)

Create Light Sources:
X 3 Overhead Lights (1 Red, 1 Green, 1 Blue) on the ceiling (Draw a colored ball to represent the light source position/color)
X Desk Lamp Light (Dim white light, about 75% intensity)
*X Bright (white) spotlight/flashlight from the camera's view (30 degrees)

Navigation (Functionality):
X Look up/down (90 degrees)
X Turn left/right (360 degrees)
X Move forward/backward
X Move side to side
X (PointerLockControls) Level the camera's gaze
X (SET KEYSTROKE): Set the camera back at a starting position
X Camera CANNOT walk through walls, set x and z boundaries

Other functionality:
X Display overlay with instructions (instructions/controls)
X 0-4: Turns off one of each of the lights (There are 5 lights total, see light sources above)
    X When all lights (except camera flashlight) are off, the textured picture on the wall appears ***
X (SET KEYSTROKE): The Copper Ball rolls around (in a circle) on the table top. Pressing same button stops the movement (Animation)
X (SET KEYSTROKE): The Polished Silver Ball rolls around (in a circle) on the table top. Pressing same button stops the movement (Animation)
X (SET KEYSTROKE): The dice animate (roll or spin) for a few seconds and then stop

